title: Wildcats expect tough Vestal team come playoffs
text:
Wildcats expect tough Vestal team come playoffs 
By wbng sports October 18, 2015 Updated Oct 18, 2015 at 11:51 PM EDT 
Johnson City, NY (WBNG Binghamton) The Class A playoff matchups are set: Maine-Endwell will host Union-Endicott in Week 9 and Vestal will travel to Johnson City for the second time in three weeks. 
The two just met in Week 7 and the Wildcats held on for a 34-27 victory to earn their first-ever playoff home game at Wildcat Stadium. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
After and 0-2 start, the Wildcats (4-3) have won four of their last five games. That won't really matter, however, if they lay an egg against Vestal (4-3) in the postseason. Head coach Fred Deinhardt expects another tight game come the postseason. 
"The guy are working hard and they're getting better. We had a lot of penalties. Penalties and mistakes add up over time and we still had mistakes (against Vestal)," he said. "Vestal played a tough game. Their quarterback is a great athlete and so is their fullback, so it'll be a tough game again." 
Before they meet in the playoffs, Johnson City finishes the regular season at unbeaten Elmira (7-0). Vestal visits Binghamton (5-2).
